<DOC><DOCNO> AP891024-0128 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-10-24-89 2025EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Israel-Lebanon     10-24 0251</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Israel-Lebanon,0259</SECOND><HEAD>Israeli Troops Kill Two Guerrillas</HEAD><DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Israeli troops shot and killed two guerrillasin Israel's self-declared security zone in south Lebanon onTuesday, the military command said.   The clash north of Majayoun, four miles north of the Israeliborder, came hours after the army said Israeli-backed militiamenshot and killed two other armed guerrillas in the security zone.   An army spokesman said an Israeli force on a routine patrol ofthe zone's central sector spotted a guerrilla squad and openedfire, attacking it from a short distance and killing two guerrillas.   The Israeli unit suffered no casualties, the spokesman said. Nofurther details were released.   Military officials said Soviet-designed AK-47 assault rifles,hand grenades and explosives were found near the guerrillas' bodies.   The officials were unable to say if the victims in the clashesMonday and Tuesday were Palestinian or Lebanese guerrillas. BothPalestinian and Lebanese militias have attacked Israeli soldiersand their militia allies in the Israeli-controlled zone in southLebanon.   No organization has claimed responsibility for the attacks onthe Israeli unit or the South Lebanon Army, which is trained, armedand financed by Israel.   Foreign reports have said about 500 Israeli soldiers patrol thesecurity zone, which covers 328 square miles, along with themilitia force made up mostly of Lebanese Christians.   Israel carved out the buffer zone to protect its northern borderagainst guerrilla attacks in June 1985 when it withdrew the bulk ofits troops from Lebanon after a three-year occupation.</TEXT></DOC>